Wash and dry all produce. Preheat broiler or #grill{} to high or oven to 500 degrees. Trim, then thinly slice @scallions{2}, keeping greens and whites separate. Cut @Yukon Gold potatoes{12} into ¾-inch pieces. Trim any stems from @green beans{6}, then cut into 2-inch pieces.

Place potatoes in a large #pot{} of salted water. Bring to a boil and cook until easily pierced by a knife, ~{10-12%minutes}. Using a #slotted spoon{}, transfer potatoes to a #medium bowl{}, keeping pot of boiling water on stove. Place bowl in refrigerator to cool potatoes.

Line a #baking sheet{} with aluminum foil and lightly oil with @olive oil{1}. Place @chicken thighs{12} on sheet. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Brush tops with half the @BBQ sauce{2}. Broil, bake, or grill until charred in spots, ~{5-7%minutes}. Flip and brush with remaining barbecue sauce. Broil or bake until no longer pink, ~{7-10%minutes}.

> TIP: Skip sheet if using grill, adding sauce during last 2 minutes of grilling.

Add green beans to pot with boiling water. Cook until tender but still crisp, ~{3-4%minutes}. Drain, then rinse under cold water. Shake green beans in #strainer{} over sink to dry.

Add green beans, scallion whites, @mayonnaise{2}, and @white wine vinegar{2} to bowl with potatoes. Toss to combine. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Divide potato salad between plates. Top with chicken. Garnish with scallion greens and serve.